        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Alexander Boyko",
          "email": "alexander.boyko@seagate.com",
          "date": "2017-06-06 08:42:04.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-9576 osp: skip llog_add error",
        "message": "LU-9576 osp: skip llog_add error\n\nBefore osp_sync thread start, we add llog record with generation\nmark. It is used for proceesing unlink records. We always have a\nrecords to process until it. If this record is not added, for\nexample no free slot at catalog, it`s not a critical error.\n\nThe patch introduces the defferd LLOG_GEN_REC if ENOSPC happen\nat osp_sync_init. In this case, osp_sync thread started and\ntrys to send/cancel unlinks. And when llog has space we add\ngeneration mark.\n\nThe patch adds sanity 263 test \"check mds mount with full catalog\"\nSimulate ENOSPC during llog_add for osp_sync_init.\n\nSigned-off-by: Alexander Boyko <alexander.boyko@seagate.com>\nChange-Id: I8eb07b96cad3d5b314b2c99e127346f6b8c24fe7\nSeagate-bug-id: MRP-4239\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
